WEBVTT

00:08.720 --> 00:10.600
[ Panting ]

00:33.640 --> 00:35.200
Please, please, don't...

00:35.200 --> 00:36.840
Don't hurt me.

00:36.840 --> 00:38.840
I don't want to play anymore.

00:46.640 --> 00:48.240
[ Voice altered ] You'll forfeit
the money.

00:48.240 --> 00:51.200
I don't care.

00:51.200 --> 00:53.000
I don't want to die.

00:55.720 --> 00:56.680
Fair enough.

00:58.880 --> 01:01.280
What, I -- I can go?

01:01.280 --> 01:03.440
Of course you can.

01:03.440 --> 01:07.040
-But I thought you said...
-It's just a game.

01:11.200 --> 01:12.120
Off you go.

01:14.200 --> 01:15.800
Chop-chop.

01:20.600 --> 01:24.200
No, no, no!
Don't! Please!

01:24.200 --> 01:25.680
[ Grunting ]

01:25.680 --> 01:27.360
[ Screaming ]

01:33.720 --> 01:38.200
And that little piggy
went splat!

01:38.200 --> 01:40.080
Bad luck, losers!

01:43.280 --> 01:45.120
[ Theme music plays ]

02:14.440 --> 02:17.840
"Harry and Fergus,
they're the real heroes.

02:17.840 --> 02:19.920
Found me
when no one else could.

02:19.920 --> 02:22.880
If it wasn't for them,
I'd be dead now,

02:22.880 --> 02:27.600
and my little Kylie-Marie would
be an orphan with just her dad."

02:27.600 --> 02:29.920
And, look, there's a nice photo
of the three of us.

02:31.160 --> 02:33.200
The three of us?
Where are you?

02:33.200 --> 02:35.200
That's my hand there
on the glass!

02:37.000 --> 02:39.520
Don't let the fame get to you.
Or you.

02:39.520 --> 02:42.160
Tomorrow we'll be wrapping up
fish and chips.

02:42.160 --> 02:44.200
When was the last time
you bought fish and chips?

02:44.200 --> 02:47.560
You've done amazing,
both of you.

02:47.560 --> 02:50.200
You saved that woman's life
and you caught a killer.

02:50.200 --> 02:52.720
Bloody brilliant!
Let me get you a drink.

02:52.720 --> 02:56.720
June, another round here
for the heroes of the hour.

02:56.720 --> 03:00.000
Uh, lend us 20, will you, Harry?
I'm a bit short this month.

03:05.880 --> 03:07.440
My name's Rita Duffy.

03:07.440 --> 03:09.400
Kayleigh Connor told me
where to find you.

03:09.400 --> 03:12.200
-Oh, you know Kayleigh Connor?
-Well, no.

03:12.200 --> 03:13.760
But I live over in Kimmage

03:13.760 --> 03:16.720
and one of the other mother's
at my daughter's school,

03:16.720 --> 03:18.640
her cousin works in the
hairdressers near the chip shop

03:18.640 --> 03:20.760
where Kayleigh works,
so I asked my friend to ask her

03:20.760 --> 03:22.480
to ask Kayleigh
where to come.

03:22.480 --> 03:25.440
I'm gonna have to have a word
with Kayleigh about that.

03:25.440 --> 03:27.480
Oh, don't be annoyed with her.

03:27.480 --> 03:28.880
When she found out she knew
you were the only one

03:28.880 --> 03:30.400
who could help me.

03:30.400 --> 03:32.040
-Help you with what?
-[ Sighs ]

03:33.480 --> 03:36.720
A year ago,
my husband, Ross, died.

03:36.720 --> 03:38.760
He fell
from a 10-story car park.

03:38.760 --> 03:40.120
Look, I don't want
to be rude, but --

03:40.120 --> 03:43.440
-She will anyway.
-Shut up, Glenn!

03:43.440 --> 03:47.000
The guards said it was suicide,
said he jumped.

03:47.000 --> 03:48.400
We were having money troubles,

03:48.400 --> 03:49.880
but he would never have
done something like that.

03:49.880 --> 03:51.680
He wasn't the sort.

03:51.680 --> 03:53.640
And when the guards gave me
back his possessions,

03:53.640 --> 03:57.120
first thing -- no note.

03:57.120 --> 03:59.000
Well, that proves it,
doesn't it?

03:59.000 --> 04:00.800
Does it?

04:00.800 --> 04:04.120
Well, if he did -- you know --

04:04.120 --> 04:05.840
He would've left a note
explaining.

04:05.840 --> 04:07.240
He was very thoughtful
like that.

04:07.240 --> 04:09.520
Every time
he committed suicide?

04:10.520 --> 04:12.520
Thanks.

04:12.520 --> 04:15.240
This is one of those bodycams
that the guards wear

04:15.240 --> 04:18.360
in documentaries,
but Ross didn't have one.

04:18.360 --> 04:21.760
I'd know.
So that's weird for starters.

04:21.760 --> 04:25.200
And then there's this.

04:25.200 --> 04:27.240
Found it in his bedside table.

04:30.400 --> 04:35.400
"Baker, Sheep; Gardener, Pig;
Dentist, Rabbit.

04:35.400 --> 04:39.000
Games begin
Thursday, April 29th, at noon."

04:39.000 --> 04:40.520
What's it mean?

04:40.520 --> 04:43.880
I don't know.
Ross was a gardener.

04:43.880 --> 04:45.880
I don't see what this
has to do...

04:45.880 --> 04:48.200
I didn't either,
until this morning.

04:48.200 --> 04:52.080
I was reading the papers,
and I found this.

04:56.240 --> 05:02.920
"Bus Driver, Sheep;
Florist, Pig; Butcher, Rabbit.

05:02.920 --> 05:06.000
Games begin
Thursday, April 28th, at noon."

05:06.000 --> 05:07.960
Here, that's three days
from now.

05:07.960 --> 05:10.000
That's a bit interesting, right?

05:10.000 --> 05:12.240
So will you take my case, then?

05:12.240 --> 05:14.280
I am very sorry for your loss,
Mrs. Duffy,

05:14.280 --> 05:16.200
but this isn't what we do.

05:16.200 --> 05:18.360
I've no one else to ask.

05:18.360 --> 05:20.640
Kayleigh was a one-off.

05:20.640 --> 05:23.440
I'm sorry.

05:23.440 --> 05:25.600
The answer is no.

05:26.560 --> 05:27.800
Harry!

05:29.880 --> 05:33.080
I'm sorry, all right?
I'll try and talk to her.

05:35.520 --> 05:37.040
[ Sighs ]

05:39.880 --> 05:41.440
-Has she gone?
-Yeah.

05:41.440 --> 05:44.040
But I think we should help her.
She needs help.

05:44.040 --> 05:46.200
Half the world needs help.

05:46.200 --> 05:47.600
Don't I get a say
in any of this?

05:47.600 --> 05:51.040
No.
We're not Cagney and Lacey.

05:52.440 --> 05:53.600
Who?

05:56.400 --> 05:58.680
VIVIAN: You want to know
why I'm shouting at you?

05:58.680 --> 06:01.000
I'm shouting at you because
I've had the deputy commissioner

06:01.000 --> 06:03.200
on the phone shouting at me
for the last 10 minutes.

06:03.200 --> 06:04.640
Any idea why?

06:04.640 --> 06:06.600
Do not interrupt me, Raymond.
I am not done.

06:06.600 --> 06:08.920
And the deputy commissioner
had the commissioner

06:08.920 --> 06:10.680
shouting at him before that.

06:10.680 --> 06:12.520
And do you know what
they were all shouting about?

06:12.520 --> 06:13.720
-My mother.
-How the hell did your mother

06:13.720 --> 06:15.160
find Colin Fountain?

06:15.160 --> 06:16.920
-It was a fluke. It --
-A fluke!

06:16.920 --> 06:19.160
There is a four-page spread
in the bloody newspaper

06:19.160 --> 06:21.200
making us look like
a bunch of incompetent idiots!

06:21.200 --> 06:23.440
She knows obscure plays
that no one else remembers,

06:23.440 --> 06:24.920
but it's not like
that's going to happen again.

06:24.920 --> 06:26.240
It was a one-off.

06:26.240 --> 06:29.400
For your sake,
I bloody well hope so.

06:29.400 --> 06:31.480
Have you considered
what a difficult position

06:31.480 --> 06:33.000
this puts me in?

06:33.000 --> 06:34.360
You think I like this,

06:34.360 --> 06:35.920
having to reprimand
my own husband?

06:35.920 --> 06:37.360
Well --

06:37.360 --> 06:38.720
Do not say
something facetious, Raymond.

06:38.720 --> 06:39.920
Now is not the time.

06:39.920 --> 06:43.440
D.C. says that if they find out

06:43.440 --> 06:45.840
you showed
her confidential files,

06:45.840 --> 06:49.240
you'll be in front of
professional standards.

06:49.240 --> 06:51.360
Career over Charlie,
do you understand?

06:51.360 --> 06:53.200
I do.
It won't happen again.

06:53.200 --> 06:54.960
Come on, Viv,
you know as well as I do

06:54.960 --> 06:56.960
that Charlie would never
do something like that.

06:56.960 --> 06:58.720
He has my complete backing.

06:58.720 --> 07:02.880
As touching as that display
of esprit de corps may be,

07:02.880 --> 07:04.400
he goes, you go too.

07:05.720 --> 07:08.080
And how do you think
that'll look for me, huh?

07:10.200 --> 07:12.560
Keep your mother
on a very tight leash.

07:19.600 --> 07:21.720
[ Doorbell ringing ]

07:21.720 --> 07:23.360
[ Knocking on door ]

07:23.360 --> 07:24.600
FERGUS: Harry?

07:24.600 --> 07:27.920
-Harry, are you there?
-Oh, shit.

07:27.920 --> 07:31.000
Oh, shit.
Stupid bell!

07:31.000 --> 07:33.000
Harry, open up!
I've found something!

07:40.280 --> 07:43.560
Ugh.
You actually look green.

07:49.960 --> 07:51.640
HARRY:
What are you doing?

07:51.640 --> 07:52.800
Hangover cure.

07:52.800 --> 07:55.200
I don't get hangovers.

07:55.200 --> 07:56.440
Oh, sound, yeah.

07:56.440 --> 07:58.200
Whatever-you've-got cure,
then.

07:58.200 --> 07:59.440
You got any Tabasco?

07:59.440 --> 08:01.280
Are you just trying
to torture me?

08:01.280 --> 08:04.440
No.
That is just a bonus.

08:04.440 --> 08:05.880
Did a little research
on the Internet

08:05.880 --> 08:08.240
when I got home yesterday.

08:08.240 --> 08:10.280
Looked up
the newspaper's website.

08:10.280 --> 08:12.480
Found the advert from last year.

08:12.480 --> 08:15.600
The baker, gardener,
dentist one.

08:15.600 --> 08:18.360
Oh, no. Not that one.
No, no, I'm so not interested.

08:18.360 --> 08:20.000
You're about to be.

08:24.240 --> 08:26.040
That's from two years ago.

08:29.680 --> 08:34.920
"Chemist, Sheep; Guard, Pig;
Teacher, Rabbit.

08:34.920 --> 08:38.680
Games begin
Thursday, April 30th, at noon."

08:38.680 --> 08:41.000
I went back further,
but there weren't any more.

08:41.960 --> 08:43.440
So?

08:46.400 --> 08:49.680
One on the left is about
the death of Ross Duffy,

08:49.680 --> 08:52.480
and that was written
a few days after he died.

08:52.480 --> 08:54.480
The one on the right,
that was published

08:54.480 --> 08:57.880
on the exact same day
as the one on the left.

08:57.880 --> 09:00.400
Now, this one's about a man
called Trevor Farrelly,

09:00.400 --> 09:02.200
drowned in the Liffey.

09:02.200 --> 09:04.720
Please, would you just
get to the point, or stab me?

09:04.720 --> 09:06.440
Just pick one.

09:06.440 --> 09:10.240
Third paragraph down.
Look what he did for a living!

09:15.200 --> 09:16.960
HARRY:
So he was a dentist.

09:16.960 --> 09:18.920
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

09:18.920 --> 09:21.080
Three people listed in the ad --

09:21.080 --> 09:24.760
a baker,
a gardener, and a dentist.

09:24.760 --> 09:27.680
Two of them died
on the same day.

09:31.280 --> 09:33.600
In the newspaper two years ago,

09:33.600 --> 09:36.640
when that advert was chemist,
guard, teacher --

09:36.640 --> 09:38.840
two stories, right?

09:38.840 --> 09:42.480
One about a teacher who was
stabbed in a local park,

09:42.480 --> 09:44.760
and on the same day a chemist

09:44.760 --> 09:48.480
was found hanging
from a tree in the woods.

09:48.480 --> 09:52.280
In the last two years,
three people identified

09:52.280 --> 09:55.400
by their jobs
were listed in an ad,

09:55.400 --> 09:58.680
and every year two people
with matching jobs die

09:58.680 --> 09:59.960
on the same day!

09:59.960 --> 10:01.880
That's not a coincidence.

10:01.880 --> 10:03.280
Yes, you're right,

10:03.280 --> 10:07.960
but what's with
the sheep, pig, rabbit?

10:07.960 --> 10:10.240
-What's that supposed to mean?
-No idea.

10:10.240 --> 10:12.960
But now are we going
to take the case?

10:12.960 --> 10:15.240
Oh, God, listen to you!

10:15.240 --> 10:18.720
Take the case?
We're not private eyes.

10:18.720 --> 10:20.880
Oh, hang about.
We found Kayleigh Connor.

10:20.880 --> 10:22.720
I found Kayleigh Connor.

10:22.720 --> 10:24.160
And I saved your arse!

10:24.160 --> 10:26.000
For which I am
extremely grateful

10:26.000 --> 10:27.760
but we're not starting
a detective agency.

10:27.760 --> 10:29.920
We're not Batman and Robin!

10:29.920 --> 10:31.840
Okay, now,
that reference I get.

10:31.840 --> 10:33.920
At least more than
"Candy and Larry."

10:33.920 --> 10:36.000
-Cagney and Lacey.
-All right, whatever.

10:36.000 --> 10:38.760
But come on, Harry,
you've got to admit,

10:38.760 --> 10:40.760
it is interesting, right?

10:42.040 --> 10:44.960
Yeah.
But I'm not doing it.

10:44.960 --> 10:47.720
Ohh!
I get it, okay?

10:47.720 --> 10:49.680
You can't face it right now.

10:56.720 --> 10:58.760
Drink that.
All in one go.

10:58.760 --> 11:00.400
It's easier that way.

11:00.400 --> 11:02.280
If you stop, you'll never take
a second sip.

11:02.280 --> 11:05.920
-Oh!
-Yeah, it's absolutely horrible.

11:05.920 --> 11:07.280
But it works.

11:07.280 --> 11:08.920
I made loads of those
over the years.

11:08.920 --> 11:12.040
10 minutes,
you'll be right as rain.

11:12.040 --> 11:14.120
Call me when you're ready.

11:16.200 --> 11:18.040
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

11:40.520 --> 11:42.360
[ Sighs ]

12:08.640 --> 12:11.920
♪ You did everything
to hurt me♪

12:11.920 --> 12:13.760
♪ Everything to burn me♪

12:13.760 --> 12:17.040
♪ Everything that's in my life♪

12:18.600 --> 12:21.120
[ Doorbell rings ]

12:21.120 --> 12:24.920
♪ Ever think
I'd love you twice? ♪

12:29.720 --> 12:30.960
Charlie's not home yet.

12:30.960 --> 12:33.080
Oh, I'll wait.

12:41.880 --> 12:44.200
Mmm.

12:44.200 --> 12:45.200
Oh.

12:50.840 --> 12:52.680
Do you know, I'm not sure
how long he's gonna be.

12:52.680 --> 12:54.000
I can always give him a message.

12:54.000 --> 12:55.360
It'll just save you
hanging around.

12:55.360 --> 12:57.320
No rush.

12:59.440 --> 13:02.240
You know, we never seem
to chat these days.

13:02.240 --> 13:05.000
Chat?
What about?

13:05.000 --> 13:06.760
I don't know.
[ Laughs ]

13:06.760 --> 13:08.440
Done anything interesting?

13:08.440 --> 13:10.240
Ever?

13:10.240 --> 13:13.200
I think we have rather different
definitions of interesting.

13:13.200 --> 13:15.680
Mm, probably.
Hmm.

13:17.200 --> 13:20.120
Oh!
How's work?

13:20.120 --> 13:22.720
You've never asked me
about work before.

13:22.720 --> 13:25.520
-Do you even know what I do?
-Course I do!

13:25.520 --> 13:31.000
You're a person that does
that thing people need.

13:31.000 --> 13:33.000
I'm a senior actuarial analyst.

13:33.000 --> 13:35.000
I mean, of course I knew that.

13:35.880 --> 13:37.760
Must be fascinating.

13:37.760 --> 13:39.640
It is actually, yeah.

13:39.640 --> 13:43.240
So I work with insurance
companies to assess risk

13:43.240 --> 13:45.200
using mathematical
and statistical analysis --

13:45.200 --> 13:47.400
Which reminds me,
is my granddaughter home?

13:47.400 --> 13:50.600
Sorry, no, it's Tuesday,
so Tuesdays is gymnastics.

13:50.600 --> 13:53.760
She won't be back till later.
How did that remind you of Lola?

13:53.760 --> 13:55.280
Oh I -- I was thinking
about careers.

13:55.280 --> 13:57.360
I mean she's that age,
isn't she?

13:58.920 --> 14:01.240
I thought I should spend
some more time with her.

14:01.240 --> 14:03.440
Why would you want to do that?

14:03.440 --> 14:06.720
Well, a girl should get
to know her grandmother.

14:06.720 --> 14:08.200
And she'll be looking
for direction,

14:08.200 --> 14:10.560
and I could be
very useful there.

14:10.560 --> 14:14.120
I could, uh, nudge her
on the right path, hmm?

14:14.120 --> 14:15.880
No, Lola knows exactly
what she's doing.

14:15.880 --> 14:17.720
We've -- We've planned it
all out.

14:17.720 --> 14:19.400
What, her entire life?

14:19.400 --> 14:21.800
-[ Door opens ]
-We're in here!

14:21.800 --> 14:23.280
[ Door closes ]

14:23.280 --> 14:25.440
Oh, hello, Charlie.

14:25.440 --> 14:27.680
Just five minutes of your time,
then I'll be out of your hair.

14:27.680 --> 14:29.600
It's not a good time.
Can it wait?

14:29.600 --> 14:32.200
Uh, two people
are about to die, so no.

14:32.200 --> 14:33.680
Oh, not this again.
I am begging you.

14:33.680 --> 14:35.600
Look, I am absolutely not
getting involved this time.

14:35.600 --> 14:37.120
I am just going to tell you
what I know,

14:37.120 --> 14:38.960
and then you can go ahead
and do your job.

14:38.960 --> 14:40.520
Oh, the job I almost lost today.

14:40.520 --> 14:42.360
-What?
-Remember my boss, Ray,

14:42.360 --> 14:44.200
and his wife,
the assistant commissioner?

14:44.200 --> 14:45.640
She's not best pleased with me.

14:45.640 --> 14:47.400
She can't understand how
you found Colin Fountain

14:47.400 --> 14:49.080
and thinks I helped.

14:49.080 --> 14:51.200
Well, I'm very happy
to tell her you did sod-all.

14:51.200 --> 14:53.680
This happens again, I'm up in
front of a disciplinary board.

14:53.680 --> 14:57.080
Well, I'm very sorry, Charlie,
but this is not my fault.

14:57.080 --> 14:58.640
If you'd just listened to me
the first time.

14:58.640 --> 14:59.960
Only time!
This never happens again.

14:59.960 --> 15:01.920
Are you listening?

15:01.920 --> 15:03.120
Yes, fine.

15:04.880 --> 15:06.440
But there's one thing you --

15:06.440 --> 15:08.560
No!
Why can't you understand!

15:08.560 --> 15:09.920
If you keep doing this,
I'm gonna lose my job.

15:09.920 --> 15:12.120
Your job is to stop murderers.

15:12.120 --> 15:13.400
There are two murders
are gonna happen.

15:13.400 --> 15:15.000
Stop talking!
You don't know that!

15:15.000 --> 15:16.120
You couldn't possibly know that!

15:17.440 --> 15:19.720
You look very stressed.

15:21.120 --> 15:23.640
You know, I think I'm gonna have
another glass

15:23.640 --> 15:26.240
of this delicious wine...

15:27.800 --> 15:31.520
...and then Orla can take you to
the bedroom and sort you out.

15:31.520 --> 15:33.280
-ORLA: Oh!
-What?

15:33.280 --> 15:34.480
HARRY: Stress.

15:34.480 --> 15:35.840
It's the number-one killer

15:35.840 --> 15:37.400
of men in your age bracket.

15:37.400 --> 15:40.480
And then when you come back down
all loosey-goosey,

15:40.480 --> 15:42.360
and then I can tell you
what I know

15:42.360 --> 15:44.560
and make you listen
to me for once.

15:47.840 --> 15:49.720
You wouldn't listen when I tried
to tell you

15:49.720 --> 15:51.040
about the last killer!

15:52.680 --> 15:53.560
[ Exhales sharply ]

16:09.480 --> 16:11.000
Ahh!

16:11.000 --> 16:12.760
Don't look smug.

16:12.760 --> 16:15.920
Smug? Moi?

16:17.400 --> 16:19.520
All right, come on.
What are we doing here?

16:20.720 --> 16:23.640
I went to the newspaper office
this morning.

16:23.640 --> 16:26.400
A very nice young man looked up
the records for me

16:26.400 --> 16:29.160
to see who had placed
all those adverts.

16:29.160 --> 16:30.240
Now, you wouldn't think
they'd give out

16:30.240 --> 16:32.120
that kind of information.

16:32.120 --> 16:34.240
Well, I can be very persuasive.

16:34.240 --> 16:37.400
Plus the 40 euros I gave him
didn't hurt.

16:37.400 --> 16:40.360
The adverts were placed
by one Bradley Gillen,

16:40.360 --> 16:43.360
lives at number 60.

16:43.360 --> 16:45.240
FERGUS: Ah, okay.

16:46.440 --> 16:48.440
So, what are we thinking?
What, like a serial killer?

16:49.840 --> 16:51.920
-No, I don't think so.
-Oh.

16:51.920 --> 16:54.600
I -- I saw him go in
a little while ago.

16:54.600 --> 16:57.840
He strikes me more like
an errand boy.

16:58.960 --> 17:01.960
Question is,
errand boy for whom?

17:15.760 --> 17:17.320
Bradley.

17:19.480 --> 17:24.560
I want to talk to you
about the adverts.

17:24.560 --> 17:26.920
The ones you've been placing
in the local paper

17:26.920 --> 17:28.360
these last three years.

17:28.360 --> 17:30.920
Care to comment?

17:30.920 --> 17:33.960
Look, piss off, okay?

17:33.960 --> 17:36.280
I have nothing to say to you.

17:37.640 --> 17:40.000
Besides, I don't know
what you're talking about.

17:40.000 --> 17:42.960
Confession is good
for the soul!

17:51.720 --> 17:54.800
[ Cellphone rings ]

17:54.800 --> 17:55.960
MAN: Who is this?

17:55.960 --> 17:57.200
BRADLEY:
Yeah, it's Bradley.

17:57.200 --> 17:58.920
Look, I just got doorstepped.

17:58.920 --> 18:01.400
Some woman there asking
questions about the advertising.

18:01.400 --> 18:03.120
MAN: You what?

18:03.120 --> 18:04.960
-Who was she?
-I don't know!

18:04.960 --> 18:06.520
She was asking me
to make comments

18:06.520 --> 18:08.440
on you know, different...

18:08.440 --> 18:10.440
Oi!

18:11.680 --> 18:13.840
Bradley?

18:13.840 --> 18:15.680
Bradley, you eejit,
are you there?

18:22.000 --> 18:23.880
Playing to your strengths,
I see.

18:23.880 --> 18:25.760
He phoned someone
called Gary Whelan.

18:25.760 --> 18:27.200
Told him about you.

18:27.200 --> 18:29.640
-Who's Gary Whelan?
-I don't know.

18:29.640 --> 18:30.840
But I know someone who might.

18:42.680 --> 18:46.280
You know the Canary Islands?
It's not named after the birds.

18:46.280 --> 18:48.040
Named after dogs.

18:48.040 --> 18:49.360
Canary dogs?

18:49.360 --> 18:50.640
No.

18:50.640 --> 18:52.720
Latin, innit?

18:52.720 --> 18:55.200
Canariae Insulae.

18:55.200 --> 18:57.440
"Islands of the Dogs."

18:58.640 --> 19:01.080
-It's where "canine" comes from.
-What, Doctor Who's dog?

19:02.680 --> 19:05.240
-FERGUS: Da.
-Ferg.

19:05.240 --> 19:07.760
-What are you doing home?
-Can I talk to you in the hall?

19:07.760 --> 19:10.920
How are you, Fergus?
Do you want a drink?

19:10.920 --> 19:12.680
Nah, you're all right, thanks.

19:12.680 --> 19:14.640
I'm actually in a bit
of a hurry, Da, please?

19:14.640 --> 19:16.920
Go on, Malky.

19:16.920 --> 19:18.720
The boy looks like
he's gonna piss himself.

19:18.720 --> 19:21.920
We can redeal these
when you come back.

19:21.920 --> 19:23.400
I was gonna win that one.

19:23.400 --> 19:25.040
[ Laughter ]

19:30.200 --> 19:31.760
Jesus, Da.

19:31.760 --> 19:34.400
What are you doing playing cards
with bleedin' Happy for?

19:34.400 --> 19:35.880
What, you've forgotten
what he was gonna do

19:35.880 --> 19:37.280
a couple of weeks ago?

19:37.280 --> 19:40.760
No. Now, he wouldn't
have done nothing.

19:40.760 --> 19:42.400
I had that under control.

19:42.400 --> 19:45.520
Just forget it, all right?

19:45.520 --> 19:48.640
Look, do you know a guy
called Gary Whelan?

19:48.640 --> 19:50.600
Course I do.

19:50.600 --> 19:52.880
Why do you wanna know about
Gary Whelan for?

19:52.880 --> 19:55.200
-Who is he?
-Well...

19:56.720 --> 19:59.200
Bit of a mad yoke,
isn't he?

19:59.200 --> 20:01.000
Makes all his money
from gambling.

20:02.160 --> 20:05.000
But you don't want anything
to do with Gary Whelan.

20:05.000 --> 20:08.720
He's a nasty one.
Dangerous.

20:08.720 --> 20:12.280
It's all right.
I just wanted to know who he is.

20:12.280 --> 20:13.680
How do you know him?

20:13.680 --> 20:16.760
I don't.
I know his accountant.

20:16.760 --> 20:18.680
[ Chuckles ]

20:18.680 --> 20:21.400
-You know an accountant?
-Yeah.

20:21.400 --> 20:24.200
Eric.
Eric Murray.

20:24.200 --> 20:27.480
Nice fella.
Races pigeons.

20:27.480 --> 20:31.200
Has a lovely French Cumulet
called Lisa.

20:31.200 --> 20:32.440
Works out of
an old furniture shop

20:32.440 --> 20:34.280
up the road
from the snooker hall.

20:35.640 --> 20:37.760
All right.

20:37.760 --> 20:39.320
Thanks.

20:49.360 --> 20:52.200
How did you find out
about Gary Whelan?

20:52.200 --> 20:54.160
Did you call your fence?

20:54.160 --> 20:56.680
I did, yeah.
Yeah, he's an old fella.

20:56.680 --> 20:58.600
Looks after us street urchins,
you know,

20:58.600 --> 21:00.400
teaches us
how to pick a pocket or two.

21:00.400 --> 21:03.160
It's not normal, kids your age
knowing how to find gangsters.

21:03.160 --> 21:07.560
Yeah, and this is normal
behavior for a woman your age?

21:09.200 --> 21:10.680
Normal's overrated.

21:12.200 --> 21:13.520
[ Doorbell jingles ]

21:16.880 --> 21:18.600
Excuse me.

21:18.600 --> 21:20.400
Sorry, we're closed.

21:20.400 --> 21:22.520
[ Exaggerated accent ] Just
caught you in time, then.

21:22.520 --> 21:25.440
What do you have
in the way of ottomans?

21:25.440 --> 21:28.000
-I don't do ottomans, sorry.
-I'll tell you why I need one.

21:28.000 --> 21:29.200
Yeah, please don't.

21:29.200 --> 21:31.280
HARRY:
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

21:40.600 --> 21:42.600
Oh, Gina Lollobrigida.

21:42.600 --> 21:44.120
ERIC:
Never heard of her.

21:44.120 --> 21:46.520
HARRY: You've never heard
of Gina Lollobrigida?

21:47.640 --> 21:49.680
Italian actress.

21:49.680 --> 21:52.520
Huge big knockers.

21:52.520 --> 21:54.320
[ Telephone rings ]

21:55.960 --> 21:57.480
Excuse me.

21:57.480 --> 22:00.400
Did they never teach you
any manners as a child!

22:00.400 --> 22:02.600
I am talking to you!

22:02.600 --> 22:04.560
-Piss off!
-Oh!

22:09.240 --> 22:10.480
[ Ringing continues ]

22:17.240 --> 22:19.240
No ottomans.

22:19.240 --> 22:20.720
I'll try elsewhere.

22:20.720 --> 22:21.800
Yes?

22:23.200 --> 22:25.040
Oh, yes, Gary.

22:26.240 --> 22:27.720
I have the number here for you.

22:27.720 --> 22:30.200
-[ Doorbell jingles ]
-It's...

22:30.200 --> 22:31.720
That's odd.
My laptop is closed.

22:31.720 --> 22:34.400
I was just working on that.

22:34.400 --> 22:36.280
Uh, no, I have --
no, I have the number here.

22:36.280 --> 22:42.320
086 402 22 22.

22:43.520 --> 22:44.520
Okay.

22:59.360 --> 23:00.560
There was a box of those,

23:00.560 --> 23:02.480
same make as the one
Ross Duffy had on

23:02.480 --> 23:04.520
when he took a nosedive
off the car park.

23:04.520 --> 23:07.760
And I got the laptop,
but there's a problem.

23:07.760 --> 23:10.400
It is password protected.

23:10.400 --> 23:13.240
Three wrong goes and
the hard drive erases itself.

23:13.240 --> 23:15.000
And the password is not Linda.

23:15.000 --> 23:16.440
Well, how do you know
it's only three goes,

23:16.440 --> 23:17.920
and why would it be Linda?

23:17.920 --> 23:20.240
I had a go in the office
after he left,

23:20.240 --> 23:23.120
and Linda because he had
a pigeon called...

23:23.120 --> 23:26.720
Ohh. It's not called Linda.
It's called Lisa.

23:26.720 --> 23:29.720
Okay, so the password
isn't Lisa either.

23:29.720 --> 23:32.200
So we have one last try?

23:33.440 --> 23:35.120
I have a good idea.

23:35.120 --> 23:37.200
Why don't you go home
and look after your sister?

23:37.200 --> 23:39.120
What?
I'm not leaving you.

23:39.120 --> 23:40.600
Well, let's face it,
he's already seen me.

23:40.600 --> 23:41.960
It's better if he doesn't
see you.

23:41.960 --> 23:43.920
All right.

23:47.960 --> 23:49.480
HARRY:
[ Normal voice ] Lose something?

23:49.480 --> 23:51.600
Oh, God, not now.
We're closed.

23:51.600 --> 23:53.000
Laptop, maybe?

23:55.440 --> 23:58.400
I am going to be
your best friend today, Eric.

23:58.400 --> 24:01.720
What happened to your voice?
How do you know my name?

24:01.720 --> 24:06.200
Your employer has upset
some people in very high places.

24:06.200 --> 24:07.920
I think you know who I am.

24:07.920 --> 24:09.040
No.

24:11.720 --> 24:13.520
Wait, you're not saying
that you're, uh...

24:13.520 --> 24:15.280
Mm-hmm.

24:15.280 --> 24:17.400
I am going to be
your best friend

24:17.400 --> 24:19.400
because I'm going to
give you a head start.

24:19.400 --> 24:21.600
South America's lovely
this time of year.

24:21.600 --> 24:24.760
One of those
nonextradition countries.

24:24.760 --> 24:26.960
I'm not sure what's going on,

24:26.960 --> 24:28.600
but I am not a man
to be messed with.

24:31.400 --> 24:33.480
Thirty seconds, and the offer
will be rescinded.

24:33.480 --> 24:35.600
You will go to prison
for the rest of your life.

24:35.600 --> 24:39.000
Maybe you'll share a cell
with Whelan.

24:39.000 --> 24:41.200
-I don't believe you.
-Well, that's your prerogative.

24:41.200 --> 24:43.200
20 seconds.

24:43.200 --> 24:44.880
Who -- Who has he upset?

24:44.880 --> 24:46.640
Did you really think there
wouldn't be any consequences

24:46.640 --> 24:47.920
for your actions, Eric?

24:47.920 --> 24:50.200
People died.
10 seconds.

24:54.200 --> 24:57.400
Three, two, one.

24:57.400 --> 24:59.640
All right, all right.
What do you want to know?

24:59.640 --> 25:02.680
Let's start with the password
for your laptop,

25:02.680 --> 25:07.000
tell me how the game works,
and then start running.

25:15.720 --> 25:17.720
You really shouldn't be here.
You're gonna get me sacked.

25:17.720 --> 25:20.040
Don't worry.
I won't hang about.

25:20.040 --> 25:21.600
Harry, you can't just...

25:21.600 --> 25:23.520
I'm out of it, I promise.

25:24.680 --> 25:26.600
Gary Whelan.

25:26.600 --> 25:29.680
He's been running a snuff game
for the last three years.

25:29.680 --> 25:33.600
People volunteer to be hunted
to death, if you can believe it.

25:33.600 --> 25:37.280
Three start, two die,
100k to the last man standing.

25:37.280 --> 25:39.640
People gamble their lives
for 100 grand?

25:39.640 --> 25:42.880
The person I spoke to said
they'd do it for a lot less.

25:42.880 --> 25:44.360
It takes a certain type,
apparently.

25:44.360 --> 25:46.400
They think
they're indestructible.

25:46.400 --> 25:48.160
Well, most do.

25:48.160 --> 25:51.760
Occasionally
they're just desperate.

25:51.760 --> 25:54.520
People follow it
on the dark web.

25:54.520 --> 25:56.960
I suppose you've heard of that.
I hadn't.

25:56.960 --> 26:00.000
It is live-streamed
rather than recorded.

26:00.000 --> 26:01.640
People bet on the outcome,

26:01.640 --> 26:04.600
and that is how Gary Whelan
makes his money.

26:04.600 --> 26:08.360
lovelylisa74, all lowercase.

26:08.360 --> 26:10.720
Everything you need is in here,

26:10.720 --> 26:13.920
including how you can
catch them all at noon tomorrow.

26:13.920 --> 26:15.600
Bloody hell, Harry.

26:15.600 --> 26:17.840
The only thing I haven't been
able to discover yet

26:17.840 --> 26:19.360
is who does the killing.

26:19.360 --> 26:21.200
Only Whelan knows that.

26:21.200 --> 26:24.480
But I do know the killer wears
a plague doctor mask.

26:24.480 --> 26:27.200
-A what?
-A horrible hooked-beak thing.

26:27.200 --> 26:31.000
You'd recognize it
if you saw it.

26:31.000 --> 26:33.440
I'm done, I promise.

26:33.440 --> 26:34.960
I wanted to make it up to you

26:34.960 --> 26:38.400
for getting you into trouble
with your boss.

26:38.400 --> 26:41.000
This is all for you to do with
as you please.

26:41.000 --> 26:46.240
Use it or chuck it in the bin,
as you see fit.

26:46.240 --> 26:47.840
Only don't do the second thing.

26:49.200 --> 26:52.560
Nobody has to know
that I was ever involved.

27:03.680 --> 27:05.920
No need to look worried.
I'm not here interfering.

27:05.920 --> 27:09.880
I came here to apologize
to Charlie.

27:09.880 --> 27:13.200
I heard you had to reprimand him
because of me.

27:13.200 --> 27:17.680
I know you and Charlie
are close.

27:17.680 --> 27:19.360
He speaks very highly of you.

27:19.360 --> 27:20.880
Not to my face he doesn't.

27:20.880 --> 27:22.720
Well, no one likes a suck-up.

27:22.720 --> 27:25.480
Ha, quite right.

27:25.480 --> 27:28.960
He says that you're the reason
he's as good a copper as he is.

27:28.960 --> 27:30.680
Funny, we've never met before.

27:30.680 --> 27:32.200
Well, we still haven't
really met.

27:32.200 --> 27:34.360
Briefly that time at Charlie's,

27:34.360 --> 27:36.640
and you said
you'd never heard of me.

27:36.640 --> 27:39.640
Well, I had a lot on my mind
that night.

27:39.640 --> 27:43.200
Yeah, don't we both know it.

27:43.200 --> 27:45.680
Well, let's hope our paths
cross again

27:45.680 --> 27:48.280
sometime soon,
Chief Superintendent.

27:48.280 --> 27:50.040
Call me Ray.

27:51.640 --> 27:53.440
Harry.

27:53.440 --> 27:55.000
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

27:58.440 --> 27:59.840
I'm so sorry.

27:59.840 --> 28:00.880
Did you have any idea...

28:00.880 --> 28:02.360
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

28:04.240 --> 28:06.680
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

28:06.680 --> 28:08.000
You know what,
if there's anything,

28:08.000 --> 28:10.600
anything at all
that we can do...

28:17.400 --> 28:19.960
[ Tense music plays ]

28:52.160 --> 28:54.560
These are to be worn
at all times.

28:56.400 --> 29:01.760
The rules are simple --
You can run but you can't hide.

29:04.600 --> 29:08.360
For the next 24 hours,
you'll keep out in the open

29:08.360 --> 29:10.480
and you'll keep moving.

29:10.480 --> 29:15.840
Because remember --
You are being hunted.

29:15.840 --> 29:18.400
And you see this guy?

29:18.400 --> 29:22.760
My condolences
because you're already dead.

29:23.960 --> 29:26.880
Two of you I won't see again.

29:26.880 --> 29:31.400
But whichever
one of you survives,

29:31.400 --> 29:34.000
I've got 100,000 euro
with your name on it.

29:34.000 --> 29:36.080
[ Snorts ]

29:36.080 --> 29:40.440
So, let's get this show
on the road, shall we?

29:40.440 --> 29:42.880
You have an hour's head start,
which begins...

29:42.880 --> 29:44.800
[ Sirens wailing,
vehicles approaching ]

29:44.800 --> 29:47.040
[ Tires screeching ]

29:47.040 --> 29:49.440
-Stand still!
-Freeze!

29:49.440 --> 29:50.720
Everyone stay
right where they are!

29:50.720 --> 29:51.720
On your knees!

29:51.720 --> 29:52.720
Hands behind your head!

29:52.720 --> 29:54.040
Stand still!

29:54.040 --> 29:55.600
[ Indistinct shouting ]

30:08.600 --> 30:09.880
[ Saxophone music playing ]

30:09.880 --> 30:12.560
Well done, dear.
I saw it on the news.

30:12.560 --> 30:14.480
Good bust.

30:14.480 --> 30:16.440
Is that the right lingo,
or have you changed that?

30:16.440 --> 30:19.040
Tell me exactly where you are,
right now.

30:19.040 --> 30:20.440
What are you --
what's going on?

30:20.440 --> 30:23.440
-There's a new advert.
-What?

30:23.440 --> 30:24.320
Hold a sec.

30:32.920 --> 30:34.680
Bollocks.

30:34.680 --> 30:36.440
Whelan lawyered up
almost immediately.

30:36.440 --> 30:38.440
He's refusing to cooperate.

30:38.440 --> 30:40.400
I want you at the station.
You'll be safe here.

30:40.400 --> 30:42.440
I don't think that's true.

30:42.440 --> 30:44.360
Now, there's something
I missed.

30:45.480 --> 30:47.400
Look at the first advert.

30:47.400 --> 30:51.400
A guard was listed
and two men died.

30:51.400 --> 30:54.240
The contestants
are complicit, Charlie.

30:54.240 --> 30:57.000
It means that there's a bent
copper out there somewhere.

30:57.000 --> 30:59.520
Could still be working today,
could even be at your station.

30:59.520 --> 31:01.040
No.
No way.

31:01.040 --> 31:02.600
How did they know
that I'm involved?

31:02.600 --> 31:04.120
Who did you tell?

31:04.120 --> 31:05.960
No one. I kept you out of it
like we agreed.

31:05.960 --> 31:09.560
Maybe someone overhead us
when I was there yesterday.

31:09.560 --> 31:11.920
Not a chance. I vouch for every
man and woman in my station.

31:11.920 --> 31:13.920
I know you do.

31:13.920 --> 31:15.520
[ Sighs ]
And that's why I can't come in.

31:15.520 --> 31:17.040
I'm sorry, Charlie.

31:22.200 --> 31:23.800
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

31:30.200 --> 31:32.080
MAN:
Hello, and good morning.

31:32.080 --> 31:34.280
I'm looking for
a Professor Wild.

31:34.280 --> 31:36.480
My name is Cian O'Mara.

31:36.480 --> 31:37.920
Hello?

31:37.920 --> 31:40.480
Yes, yes. I'm here.
Who's this?

31:40.480 --> 31:42.280
Ah, good, excellent.

31:42.280 --> 31:44.400
Look, I won't
beat around the bush.

31:44.400 --> 31:46.440
I'm a journalist over
at The Times,

31:46.440 --> 31:48.760
and I've been tracking
these people too.

31:48.760 --> 31:50.480
What?

31:50.480 --> 31:52.880
Yes, the snuff game,
Gary Whelan, all of it.

31:52.880 --> 31:55.440
But you've got a lot closer
than me, and, well,

31:55.440 --> 31:57.440
I've been at it
for over a year.

31:57.440 --> 32:00.000
Listen, maybe we can
help each other.

32:00.000 --> 32:01.400
[ Saxophone music playing
through phone ]

32:01.400 --> 32:02.280
Hello?

32:04.640 --> 32:06.440
Is anyone there?

32:06.440 --> 32:08.600
It would be great if we could
meet up.

32:08.600 --> 32:11.000
Maybe over at the café.

32:12.000 --> 32:14.040
[ Saxophone music playing ]

32:15.680 --> 32:17.280
[ Indistinct talking ]

32:25.440 --> 32:26.560
[ Line rings ]

32:28.200 --> 32:29.440
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

32:33.400 --> 32:35.000
What's up, Harry?

32:35.000 --> 32:37.640
Listen, no time for questions.
I'm being tracked!

32:37.640 --> 32:39.960
What?
Who's tracking you?

32:39.960 --> 32:41.760
"Who" isn't important right now.

32:41.760 --> 32:43.960
How does someone track me,
and how do I stop it?

32:43.960 --> 32:46.200
Your phone probably.

32:46.200 --> 32:48.720
I mean, loads of apps
can track phones.

32:48.720 --> 32:51.480
Nothing's so precise he can
pinpoint your exact location,

32:51.480 --> 32:53.480
but if he calls,
don't answer.

32:53.480 --> 32:54.840
It'll be to flush you out.

32:54.840 --> 32:58.000
Oh, shit!
Well, how can I turn it off?

32:58.000 --> 32:59.400
Switch off your phone.

32:59.400 --> 33:01.400
Or put it in airplane mode,
right?

33:01.400 --> 33:03.520
If it's not transmitting,
he can't track it.

33:03.520 --> 33:05.200
Okay, yeah.
I can do that.

33:05.200 --> 33:07.800
All right.
You got anywhere to go?

33:10.640 --> 33:13.560
I parked a good distance away
in case they're tracking my car.

33:14.760 --> 33:16.840
They do this in films
all the time.

33:23.880 --> 33:25.760
[ Thudding overhead ]

33:25.760 --> 33:29.000
Ah, don't worry about it.
Just me da.

33:29.000 --> 33:31.400
Be careful what you say
around him though.

33:31.400 --> 33:33.720
I mean, he wouldn't say anything
to anyone on purpose,

33:33.720 --> 33:37.200
but he does know
some dodgy types,

33:37.200 --> 33:40.040
which is how I knew
where to find Gary Whelan.

33:42.200 --> 33:44.000
Da.

33:44.000 --> 33:47.720
You remember Miss Cassidy
from social services.

33:47.720 --> 33:50.520
She's here to observe us
for a few days.

33:50.520 --> 33:53.600
We got the letter, remember?

33:54.560 --> 33:57.000
Ohh, yeah.

33:58.200 --> 33:59.680
Right.

33:59.680 --> 34:01.880
That's today, is it?

34:01.880 --> 34:03.200
Nothing to worry about.

34:03.200 --> 34:05.000
As long as you haven't
broken any rules.

34:05.000 --> 34:09.680
Well, rules are rules.

34:11.480 --> 34:15.640
It's just that I got to see
a man about a...

34:15.640 --> 34:17.960
Yeah.
Don't worry about it, Da.

34:17.960 --> 34:19.480
I'm sure I can deal
with everything.

34:19.480 --> 34:22.240
Great.

34:22.240 --> 34:24.200
That okay, Missus -- uh...?

34:24.200 --> 34:25.200
Mm-hmm.

34:25.200 --> 34:31.200
Just, you know, bad timing.

34:31.200 --> 34:32.720
No problem, Mr. Reid.

34:34.200 --> 34:36.760
Okay.
There we go.

34:38.200 --> 34:39.760
Some nice people here,
you know?

34:39.760 --> 34:41.920
It's like a community.

34:41.920 --> 34:44.680
Always someone to look after
Liberty if I need.

34:44.680 --> 34:47.800
I don't need looking after.
I'm almost eight.

34:49.080 --> 34:51.040
-Are you Harry?
-I am!

34:52.200 --> 34:53.360
How did you know?

34:53.360 --> 34:55.760
He's always going on
about you --

34:55.760 --> 34:58.520
"Harry says this,
Harry says that."

34:58.520 --> 35:01.080
-Shut up, Libs!
-[ Chuckles ]

35:01.080 --> 35:02.880
Pleased to make
your acquaintance.

35:02.880 --> 35:05.880
Oh, you are very polite.

35:05.880 --> 35:10.400
My teacher Mrs. Webb says
that manners are important.

35:10.400 --> 35:12.640
She sounds like
a really great teacher.

35:12.640 --> 35:15.440
She's not. She's a right old
bitch most of the time.

35:15.440 --> 35:16.960
Oh!
Excuse me?!

35:16.960 --> 35:18.840
Go and get ready please,
stinker.

35:18.840 --> 35:20.200
See you later, Harry.

35:27.880 --> 35:29.560
What happened to your mum?

35:29.560 --> 35:31.120
Left.

35:31.120 --> 35:33.240
And you never heard
from her again?

35:34.400 --> 35:35.960
It's okay.

35:35.960 --> 35:38.720
Me Granny Jeannie
came to live here.

35:38.720 --> 35:41.600
Yeah, that was great.

35:41.600 --> 35:45.240
But, um, she died
a couple of years ago.

35:45.240 --> 35:47.680
Then it was just
the three of us again.

35:47.680 --> 35:49.760
I need to ask you something.

35:51.480 --> 35:52.720
You're not a mugger.

35:54.720 --> 35:57.080
Why did you do what you did
that day?

36:01.240 --> 36:03.200
Look, don't judge him,
all right?

36:06.040 --> 36:09.120
One day I got home

36:09.120 --> 36:12.920
and there was a fella called
Happy sitting where you are.

36:13.880 --> 36:15.600
Happy lends people money.

36:15.600 --> 36:17.480
A loan shark.

36:19.200 --> 36:22.000
Da owes him a lot,

36:22.000 --> 36:26.880
and Happy was there to collect
that week's repayment.

36:26.880 --> 36:32.200
But Da was short
by 13 euro and 26 cent.

36:35.200 --> 36:38.080
Happy was drinking
a cup of tea.

36:38.080 --> 36:42.440
He said to Malky he had
until he finished his tea

36:42.440 --> 36:44.720
to find the money,

36:44.720 --> 36:49.880
or else Happy was gonna go
upstairs into Liberty's room

36:49.880 --> 36:51.240
and break her arm.

36:51.240 --> 36:52.760
Jesus!

36:54.480 --> 36:58.240
I yelled at Malky
to do something,

36:58.240 --> 37:00.560
but he just
kept waffling on like --

37:00.560 --> 37:04.040
like he could talk him
out of it somehow.

37:05.400 --> 37:06.960
Turns out alcoholics
aren't really good

37:06.960 --> 37:09.040
in pressurized situations,
you know?

37:11.520 --> 37:12.960
Anyway...

37:14.640 --> 37:17.200
I had a few minutes
to find a solution,

37:17.200 --> 37:23.640
and you were
the first person I saw.

37:23.640 --> 37:26.960
Look, Harry, I'm sorry.

37:28.960 --> 37:30.320
I know.

37:31.720 --> 37:34.440
And you never have to say that
to me again.

37:36.200 --> 37:37.600
But your dad's a moron.

37:37.600 --> 37:40.480
Here, you're in his house.

37:40.480 --> 37:42.640
Don't go slagging off me da.

37:42.640 --> 37:45.360
-All right, he does his best.
-It's not very good.

37:45.360 --> 37:47.440
Yeah, but it's his best.

37:48.920 --> 37:50.480
He's still here.

37:51.440 --> 37:53.040
Yeah.

37:59.000 --> 38:01.000
Just need to help Libby
with her homework,

38:01.000 --> 38:04.400
then maybe we should think
about what to do next, you know?

38:04.400 --> 38:06.400
We need to find him
before he finds you.

38:06.400 --> 38:09.360
-Agreed.
-What about your son?

38:09.360 --> 38:12.240
He'd just call in his squad.

38:12.240 --> 38:15.240
He trusts them, and any one
of them could be on the inside.

38:15.240 --> 38:17.640
And if he didn't,
it would scrap his career.

38:17.640 --> 38:20.720
No, I have to sort this out
without Charlie,

38:20.720 --> 38:22.440
somewhere that
I control things,

38:22.440 --> 38:25.000
somewhere I know

38:25.000 --> 38:28.960
that Mr. Plague Doctor
Psycho Nutcase doesn't.

38:28.960 --> 38:31.680
Yeah, we'll work it out.
Back in a tic.

38:33.280 --> 38:34.800
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

39:10.400 --> 39:11.280
FERGUS: Harry?

39:25.400 --> 39:27.520
HARRY: Worked it out,
but you can't be part of it.

39:27.520 --> 39:29.400
Too dangerous.

39:29.400 --> 39:31.960
What would happen to Liberty
if you weren't here?

39:31.960 --> 39:34.760
I know what I'm doing.

39:34.760 --> 39:36.560
You're a good man, Fergus.

39:41.240 --> 39:43.240
[ Exhales sharply ]

39:46.200 --> 39:47.040
[ Glass breaks ]

39:48.520 --> 39:50.040
[ Thud ]

40:06.520 --> 40:07.520
Shit.

40:13.160 --> 40:18.400
[ Voice altered ] These blades
are 600 years old.

40:18.400 --> 40:23.160
We were up to a descendant
of a real-life samurai master.

40:23.160 --> 40:28.200
This steel has been folded
a thousand times.

40:28.200 --> 40:31.120
It costs a fortune.

40:31.120 --> 40:35.800
And we've been saving it
for a special occasion.

40:37.400 --> 40:44.200
Tell me, why are you
running around hunting people?

40:44.200 --> 40:46.040
Teach you that
at St. Edmund's, did they?

40:49.440 --> 40:53.120
"Up to a descendent
of a real-life samurai."

40:53.120 --> 40:56.240
Anyone else would've said
"taught by."

40:56.240 --> 40:58.920
"Up to's"
so drearily St. Ed's.

40:58.920 --> 41:00.880
Lucky guess.

41:00.880 --> 41:05.200
Not here afterwards,
uh, over the water.

41:05.200 --> 41:07.800
Oxford.

41:07.800 --> 41:09.760
Balliol College.

41:12.000 --> 41:14.640
Now, that -- that was a guess.

41:14.640 --> 41:17.120
It's your voice.

41:17.120 --> 41:19.840
I can hear that
overprivileged sneer.

41:21.640 --> 41:23.480
Although it is somewhat muffled

41:23.480 --> 41:26.080
with these ridiculous masks
you're wearing.

41:28.200 --> 41:29.680
Do take them off.

41:30.760 --> 41:33.120
RED MASK:
Enough of this foreplay.

41:33.120 --> 41:36.960
Let's get to the stabbing
and the cutting.

41:39.800 --> 41:42.720
Move! Go!

41:42.720 --> 41:44.600
Go back around!
Go!

41:44.600 --> 41:46.440
[ Indistinct shouting ]

41:46.440 --> 41:48.360
[ Dramatic music playing ]

41:52.440 --> 41:53.560
That way!

42:20.600 --> 42:22.040
Oi, oi!

42:30.960 --> 42:32.520
[ Banging on door ]

42:51.800 --> 42:53.480
Ah!

42:53.480 --> 42:55.480
Oh! Oh!
My leg!

42:57.520 --> 42:58.360
[ Groaning ]

43:20.880 --> 43:23.680
Where are you,
you interfering bitch?

43:23.680 --> 43:25.080
[ Whispering ] Oh, rude.

43:31.000 --> 43:33.080
[ Laughs ]

43:33.080 --> 43:36.120
Has somebody been watching
too much "Scooby-Doo"?

43:47.520 --> 43:48.520
Aah!

43:48.520 --> 43:50.000
Uh!

43:50.000 --> 43:52.040
[ Grunts ]

43:52.040 --> 43:53.040
[ Whimpers ]

43:54.600 --> 43:57.560
Why couldn't you just mind
your own business?

43:57.560 --> 43:59.040
What?

44:01.040 --> 44:04.080
I can't understand anything
you say. You're mumbling.

44:04.080 --> 44:05.760
Look, if you're going
to kill me,

44:05.760 --> 44:09.680
just -- just take off
that bloody ridiculous mask.

44:14.200 --> 44:18.200
How would you ever know
someone like Gary Whelan?

44:18.200 --> 44:19.720
[ Normal voice ]
You know the saying --

44:19.720 --> 44:21.200
The only
way to get rid of temptation

44:21.200 --> 44:23.160
is to yield to it.

44:23.160 --> 44:26.040
Whelan is a man
who helps one yield.

44:26.040 --> 44:29.360
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]

44:29.360 --> 44:32.520
Don't get excited.
They're not for us.

44:32.520 --> 44:34.440
But they are.

44:34.440 --> 44:37.400
Didn't I mention?

44:37.400 --> 44:41.000
It's been live-streaming
ever since the lecture hall.

44:42.760 --> 44:45.600
You have about a minute's
head start if you're lucky.

44:53.200 --> 44:54.040
[ Screams ]

45:00.640 --> 45:02.040
[ Groans ]

45:05.720 --> 45:06.760
[ Whimpering ]

45:09.720 --> 45:12.080
-Aah!
-Oh!

45:12.080 --> 45:14.280
Jesus!
This thing's really sharp!

45:14.280 --> 45:17.880
What are you doing here?
How did you find me?

45:17.880 --> 45:20.880
I told you!
Loads of apps track phones.

45:20.880 --> 45:23.040
RED MASK: [ Moaning ]

45:23.040 --> 45:24.440
CHARLIE:
Keep the cuffs on him.

45:24.440 --> 45:26.880
Hang on till we get this lad
loaded up.

45:26.880 --> 45:28.800
Then we'll bring him in
for processing.

45:31.400 --> 45:32.960
Déjà vu, anyone?

45:32.960 --> 45:34.200
Nah, you're all right, thanks.

45:34.200 --> 45:36.240
Don't really like foreign food.

45:36.240 --> 45:37.880
Look, I'm sorry
if this causes any trouble.

45:37.880 --> 45:39.680
I really didn't mean it
to happen.

45:39.680 --> 45:41.680
Yeah, I know, but this is what
happens when you interfere

45:41.680 --> 45:42.720
in things
that don't concern you.

45:42.720 --> 45:44.480
People were dying.

45:44.480 --> 45:46.840
I couldn't just pretend
that it wasn't happening.

45:46.840 --> 45:49.000
No, of course you couldn't.

45:49.000 --> 45:51.880
So is the commissioner
gonna come down on you?

45:51.880 --> 45:53.680
We'll see.

45:53.680 --> 45:56.200
I don't know what you said
to Ray, but he's all gung ho,

45:56.200 --> 45:57.880
ready to stand up to anyone
for me.

45:57.880 --> 45:59.600
Maybe even his wife.

46:04.440 --> 46:05.480
Hmm.

46:06.800 --> 46:08.800
[ Theme music plays ]
